  5. Shadow DOM — Why It Matters for Design Systems

  Page DOM
  │
  ├── <header>
  ├── <my-button>        ← your custom element
  │       #shadow-root   ← THE WALL — nothing crosses this
  │           <button class="btn">Click</button>
  │
  └── <footer>

  - Page CSS targeting .btn will NOT affect your button's internal .btn
  - Your button's CSS targeting .btn will NOT affect the page's .btn
  - This is why design systems love Shadow DOM — guaranteed visual consistency

  The host element (<my-button> itself) is the bridge. You can style it from outside using CSS custom properties (design tokens):

  /* Page CSS — crossing the shadow boundary via CSS variables */
  my-button {
    --button-color: hotpink;
  }

  /* Inside the component */
  button {
    background: var(--button-color, blue); /* fallback to blue */
  }

